UI/UX Designer Job Responsibilities. 
Leading the design of clients’ mobile apps and websites; 
Identifying clients’ niche, conducting user experience analysis, collaborating with the marketing team; 
Developing a deep understanding of user goals and behaviors; Creating wireframes, storyboards, user flows, process flows and site maps to effectively communicate interaction and design ideas; 
Creating a tailored design based on pre-conducted analysis, which meets the user experience and user interests; 

UI/UX Designer Experience and Qualifications; 
3+ years’ experience in UI/UX design; 
Experience in structuring and designing sales funnels/landing pages; 
Good analytical skills;

Professionalism level: Senior; 

Salary: Commission-based without any upper limits; 

Working hours: Negotiable.
